snippet.textDisplay: Omg 5 yards longer really, how on gods green earth is 5 yards going to affect or benefit the amateurs game, its no wonder there not asking north of €500 for those extra 5yards. The last 3-5 years the driving equipment released by the branded manufacturers have lost the plot it's like you can come up with the latest gimmick and ask crazy money for it but the sad thing about it is there people out there that are willing to pay these extortionate prices just so they can have the latest gimmick on offer, it's not that there releasing one new driver they have to bring out 3 at a time it's madness I tell you madness.

snippet.textDisplay:
The exact same numbers in terms of distance for callaway for the past 5 years it is all advertising to make it seem that the club will make the ball go further
This is backed up by newtons law which mean the force equals to the mass times acceleration
In golf language the distance the ball goes is how fast you can swing the club times the weight of the club so all this fancy matierials mean nothing only the weight and for the past 10 years the weight has been the same so if you want a longer drive it is all down to your swing speed
